WEBVTT

00:01.569 --> 00:04.072
- Previously on The Unit.
- You have no idea
what Drake's capable of.

00:04.105 --> 00:06.274
He killed the vice president.
He launched
a chlorine attack.

00:06.307 --> 00:08.042
- Am I missing something?
- You brought a friend.

00:08.076 --> 00:10.644
- Her husband's
a Special Forces soldier.
- That's interesting.

00:10.678 --> 00:13.881
Colonel Ryan knows your wife
is missing, and he instructed me
not to inform you.

00:13.914 --> 00:16.584
I have some concerns
about Colonel Ryan's
judgment.

00:16.617 --> 00:19.053
Drop it, Jonas.

00:19.087 --> 00:21.089
Make it look good.

00:22.923 --> 00:24.892
You put my wife in danger.
My wife!

00:24.925 --> 00:27.095
And Sam McBride--
He's been working with you
all along.

00:27.128 --> 00:30.864
Sam is on the inside.
From now on we'll know
whatever he knows.

00:30.898 --> 00:36.036
- 37 kilograms of enriched
U-235 weapons-grade uranium.
- Enough for multiple bombs.

00:36.070 --> 00:39.740
If there's an attack in America
and Russian elements are behind
it, you know what that means.

00:39.773 --> 00:43.411
If you're ever ready to leave
this place, you come find me.

00:46.380 --> 00:50.318
** [ Stereo:
Man Singing Country ]

00:51.785 --> 00:54.555
Mmm.

00:54.588 --> 00:57.891
I was told I can find
what I'm looking for here.

00:57.925 --> 01:00.261
I profoundly hope so.

01:02.363 --> 01:05.533
Very nice.
Any more on the menu?

01:07.135 --> 01:10.804
[ Bell Ringing ]
I would be surprised
if we can't suit your taste.

01:19.046 --> 01:23.151
My, oh, my. Hmm.

01:27.955 --> 01:31.159
You keep looking at me
like that, you might
give a girl ideas.

01:33.161 --> 01:35.496
And what will you
give me in return?

01:35.529 --> 01:37.298
Whiplash.

01:46.207 --> 01:48.642
[ Chattering ]

02:08.095 --> 02:10.398
- You still on the team?
- Never left it.

02:10.431 --> 02:13.567
That's quite a cover
you built for yourself,
Whiplash.

02:13.601 --> 02:18.772
- Thank you, Sergeant.
- Rapist, spree shooter,
terrorist henchman.

02:18.806 --> 02:21.675
I stepped on a couple of toes
during the pantomime.

02:21.709 --> 02:24.077
I only regret
what I put Bridget through.

02:24.111 --> 02:26.614
You were on a mission.

02:28.682 --> 02:31.319
- [ Sighs ]
Drake's waiting on me.
- Where is he now?

02:31.352 --> 02:34.555
He's down the road.
I told him I needed to
relieve a little tension.

02:34.588 --> 02:36.657
He sympathize?
He seemed to.

02:36.690 --> 02:38.992
This uranium--
Tell me about it.

02:39.026 --> 02:42.930
Thirty-seven kilos
of Russian U-235.

02:42.963 --> 02:45.766
Drake says it's
been weaponized already.
Weaponized where?

02:45.799 --> 02:49.169
He says it's stashed
in some storefront
in Atlanta.

02:49.203 --> 02:52.039
We're driving down
tomorrow to meet up with
the rest of the team.

02:52.072 --> 02:55.243
Okay. I'll tail you
to Atlanta.

02:55.276 --> 02:57.678
If I may?
All right.

02:57.711 --> 03:00.914
This guy's good.
He picks up on you,
he'll abort the plan.

03:00.948 --> 03:04.418
No. Step up in Atlanta.
We'll be together there.

03:04.452 --> 03:06.487
What's the target?
I don't know.

03:06.520 --> 03:08.589
You don't know?
He hasn't told me yet.

03:08.622 --> 03:11.559
- Don't he trust you?
- He's working on it.

03:14.462 --> 03:16.530
I'll see you in Georgia.

03:18.065 --> 03:19.933
See you there.

03:22.102 --> 03:23.837
[ Door Closes ]

03:25.739 --> 03:27.575
I.D., please?

03:28.942 --> 03:32.012
Helo touches down in Atlanta
with Alpha Bravo in 10.

03:32.045 --> 03:36.016
I need to see every little crook
and nanny in a five-block radius
up on that board.

03:36.049 --> 03:40.754
Sir, the commander
of Georgia State Patrol
has 12 units ready to move.

03:40.788 --> 03:43.090
- Atlanta SWAT with four more.
- Is he deaf or disrespectful?

03:43.123 --> 03:44.825
I told him no outsiders
on this one.

03:44.858 --> 03:47.328
Mayor's office
is on line five. He'd like to
clear residents from the block.

03:47.361 --> 03:50.264
Negative. Drake sees
anything out of the ordinary,
he'll flinch.

03:50.298 --> 03:52.900
- Sir, the mayor's concerned
about collateral damage.
- Is he now?

03:52.933 --> 03:56.704
-Sir, he is.
-That'll be a drop in the bucket
if we don't do this right.

04:01.174 --> 04:05.245
We'd better push it
if we're gonna make Atlanta
before sundown.

04:05.279 --> 04:08.181
We're running late.
Uh-huh.

04:08.215 --> 04:11.319
Give me your phone.
I'll call ahead.
No. Not necessary.

04:22.496 --> 04:25.766
- What is this now?
- Gotta shake things up.

04:40.247 --> 04:42.883
End of the road.

04:46.520 --> 04:49.323
I thought
the end of the road
was Atlanta.

04:49.357 --> 04:52.225
- No. The end
of the road's here.
- Smart.

04:52.259 --> 04:54.662
Thank you.

04:59.433 --> 05:02.002
Last looks, gentlemen.

05:02.035 --> 05:05.305
If you have any questions,
share them with me.

05:07.040 --> 05:09.643
No?

05:09.677 --> 05:12.913
Your cash, itineraries
out of the country,

05:12.946 --> 05:14.782
secure phones.

05:16.350 --> 05:18.652
Directions
to your targets inside.

05:19.587 --> 05:21.755
St. Louis,
Philadelphia, Dallas.

05:25.959 --> 05:28.496
Park your vehicles
where instructed...

05:28.529 --> 05:30.598
and get out of
the blast zone quickly,

05:30.631 --> 05:34.835
unless you want
the mother of all tans.

05:34.868 --> 05:36.670
[ Chuckling ]

05:42.943 --> 05:44.812
There you go.

05:48.582 --> 05:51.885
I thought there was
only one bomb.
I know you did.

05:57.024 --> 05:59.560
In the backseat,
where you can keep
an eye on the weapon.

05:59.593 --> 06:01.795
Drive the speed limit.
Don't run any reds.

06:01.829 --> 06:04.798
And for God's sake,
easy over the potholes.

06:04.832 --> 06:07.601
- None for me?
- You and I have
other business.

06:07.635 --> 06:10.003
Let's hear it.
[ Engine Starts ]

06:10.037 --> 06:12.773
We have a friend in high places
who's been very helpful to us.

06:12.806 --> 06:15.543
A mole.
Now it's time
to return the favor.

06:20.247 --> 06:23.984
When the attacks go down,
suspicion will eventually
fall on him.

06:24.017 --> 06:26.153
We're gonna get him
out of the country first.

06:26.186 --> 06:29.790
"E" and "E."
That is your specialty?
That is correct.

06:29.823 --> 06:32.192
Well, that is what
you're gonna do.

06:32.225 --> 06:34.227
Who is he?

06:34.261 --> 06:36.129
You'll recognize him.

06:47.007 --> 06:50.177
Surf's up, baby bro.
Could you move a little faster?

06:52.580 --> 06:54.482
What do you do
when you see Indians?

06:54.515 --> 06:56.850
Be careful.

06:56.884 --> 06:59.252
What do you do
when you don't see Indians?

06:59.286 --> 07:01.154
Be twice as careful.
I hear you.

07:02.355 --> 07:05.726
Betty Blue,
we have eyes on.

07:05.759 --> 07:09.563
[ Jonas On Radio ]
Bravo 3 is at your 9:00.

07:09.597 --> 07:13.100
Roger that. No movement
down here. Just a couple
of kids on skateboards.

07:13.133 --> 07:17.204
Yeah. I saw that.
We're not getting a very good
look from inside here.

07:30.050 --> 07:33.153
It's all quiet.
You'd think there'd be
some activity by now.

07:33.186 --> 07:35.523
Advance man or something.

07:46.634 --> 07:50.671
No.
This is not right.

07:52.873 --> 07:56.409
- Yeah, we should gas up
for the trip.
- Okay.

07:56.443 --> 07:59.647
I'll pump.
You get some food?
Sure.

07:59.680 --> 08:02.449
I should probably
hit the head too.

08:02.482 --> 08:04.552
[ Ratchet Whirring ]

08:08.355 --> 08:10.223
- You in there.
- Occupied.

08:12.392 --> 08:14.227
Take it easy!

08:15.362 --> 08:17.464
Hey, what the hell? Let go!

08:17.497 --> 08:19.833
All right! I'm coming!
[ Toilet Flushing ]

08:19.867 --> 08:22.235
God!

08:22.269 --> 08:25.573
What the hell's wrong
with you, man?
[ Grunts ]

08:25.606 --> 08:28.742
Do you have a cell phone?
Yeah, yeah. Take it.
It's in my back pocket.

08:28.776 --> 08:32.179
Shut up and listen.
I don't have a lot of time.

08:32.212 --> 08:35.849
I am a federal agent.
This is a phone number.

08:35.883 --> 08:38.852
I need you to call it
the moment I walk out that door.

08:38.886 --> 08:42.055
- These are all Carolina
license plates.
- All right.

08:42.089 --> 08:44.524
You tell them you got this
information from Whiplash.
Whiplash.

08:44.558 --> 08:49.029
They'll put you
on a secure line,
and you give 'em this.

08:49.062 --> 08:50.998
You're
a government agent?
That's right.

08:52.099 --> 08:54.534
And I need you
to make that call.

08:54.568 --> 08:57.805
Let's go.

08:57.838 --> 09:00.608
I waited for this jackass.

09:12.319 --> 09:14.588
Still no movement
in or out.

09:14.622 --> 09:17.490
- Bad intel?
- I think we're being conned.

09:17.524 --> 09:19.760
- By Drake or by Sam?
- Does it matter?

09:21.061 --> 09:24.164
Let's break this down.
Bravo Team in the back.

09:24.197 --> 09:27.300
Betty Blue, Dirt Diver,
meet us out front.

09:28.501 --> 09:31.338
[ Cell Phone Beeping ]

09:31.371 --> 09:33.273
[ Beeps ]
Go for Snake Doc.

09:33.306 --> 09:36.777
- Operation's scrubbed.
You're looking at a decoy.
- Is that so?

09:36.810 --> 09:39.980
New intel. The meet's
already taken place somewhere
outside of Louisville.

09:40.013 --> 09:43.183
- I understand.
- We got three plate numbers
and three cars.

09:43.216 --> 09:45.853
And here it is.
Each is carrying
a nuclear device.

09:45.886 --> 09:48.421
- Three bombs?
- That is affirmative.

09:48.455 --> 09:51.892
Okay. We can be
wheels up in 10.
Is Whiplash gonna lead us in?

09:51.925 --> 09:55.996
-Negative. Whiplash and
the bombs are in the wind.
-We got three bombs in the wind?

09:56.029 --> 09:57.364
That's right.

09:59.299 --> 10:02.836
[ Phone Beeps ]
Remember when your mama
said it could be worse?

10:03.837 --> 10:05.839
This is what she
was talking about.

10:05.873 --> 10:09.342
[ Man ]
* Give me your secrets
Bring me a sign *

10:09.376 --> 10:13.346
* Give me a reason
to walk the fire *

10:13.380 --> 10:16.116
* See another dawn

10:16.149 --> 10:17.951
* Through a daughter's eyes

10:17.985 --> 10:22.355
* You give me a reason
to walk the fire **

10:26.559 --> 10:28.628
[ Helicopter Whirring ]

10:31.031 --> 10:35.035
Snake Doctor, we have local
units in and around Louisville
tracking the vehicle tags.

10:35.068 --> 10:38.806
Traffic cams and roadway
surveillance are now also
operating in surrounding states.

10:38.839 --> 10:43.911
We're over I-65 now,
looking to put feet down fast.
Give me a target.

10:43.944 --> 10:46.146
We're trying to get you one.
Interstates are shutting down.

10:46.179 --> 10:48.281
Okay. That should force them
off onto surface streets.

10:48.315 --> 10:50.017
Too many ways to slip
out of the city.

10:50.050 --> 10:53.020
Like snakes
through a picket fence.
[ Grey ] Yeah. No doubt.

10:53.053 --> 10:56.023
Redcap, any other intel
on the third target?
Negative.

10:56.056 --> 10:58.926
Whiplash was only able
to give us two out
of the three cities.

10:58.959 --> 11:01.228
St. Louis and Dallas.
Roger that.

11:01.261 --> 11:04.798
St. Louis and Dallas only.
We'll get you a sitrep
when we land.

11:04.832 --> 11:06.934
[ Beeps ]

11:06.967 --> 11:11.271
- Dallas?
- I know your children
are in Dallas.

11:11.304 --> 11:13.907
- Yeah, that's right.
- With Kim's parents.

11:16.076 --> 11:18.678
There's a lot of people
in Dallas.

11:20.280 --> 11:22.883
Kim, which box
do these linens go in?

11:22.916 --> 11:25.418
Behind me.
Joss, you don't have to--

11:25.452 --> 11:27.855
And miss the chance
to inventory
your wardrobe?

11:27.888 --> 11:31.524
I mean, look at this. Oh, baby.

11:31.558 --> 11:34.094
[ Chuckling ]
Well, keep it for
your trousseau.

11:34.127 --> 11:36.864
I don't think I could
squeeze into that thing
after my third baby.

11:36.897 --> 11:40.768
- Oh, please. You're gorgeous.
- Never thought I'd be happy
to see Fort Griffith again.

11:40.801 --> 11:43.370
- Things change.
- You think they'll have us in
the same neighborhood, Molly?

11:43.403 --> 11:45.372
I really don't know.

11:45.405 --> 11:48.175
Well, if they end up kicking
Charlie out of the Unit
for marrying me,

11:48.208 --> 11:50.878
I'd at least like
the royal tour.

11:50.911 --> 11:52.913
Would you do me
the honors, Molly?

11:52.946 --> 11:56.216
I'd like to, Joss,
but that won't be possible.

11:56.249 --> 11:58.886
- Why?
- I won't be coming back
to Fort Griffith.

11:58.919 --> 12:03.056
- I don't understand.
- I'm leaving the army.

12:03.090 --> 12:05.325
But you and Jonas--
You're splitting up?

12:06.726 --> 12:09.162
I asked him to go with me.

12:09.196 --> 12:12.699
Well, wouldn't
that sort of be
an ultimatum?

12:12.732 --> 12:14.334
No. It's calling in a debt.

12:15.635 --> 12:18.338
When I wanted to leave Mack,
you talked me out of it.

12:18.371 --> 12:20.473
That's right.
But?

12:21.775 --> 12:24.812
Jonas intends to live
and fight forever.

12:26.013 --> 12:28.348
This soldier's tour is over.

12:33.486 --> 12:36.089
I'm stunned.

12:36.123 --> 12:38.758
- I really am stunned.
- Well--

12:41.028 --> 12:43.096
That's not my intention.

12:47.901 --> 12:49.837
How do we stop these bombs?

12:49.870 --> 12:52.705
Sir, in the last hour,
my team has hit the ground
and fanned out.

12:52.739 --> 12:55.308
We're attempting to track
the vehicles as they reach
their destination.

12:55.342 --> 12:57.610
I don't understand
what that means-- you're
"attempting" to track them.

12:57.644 --> 12:59.913
We are attempting--
You have local
law enforcement cooperation?

12:59.947 --> 13:03.283
Yes, we do, Mr. President.
What about using the news media
or AMBER Alerts?

13:03.316 --> 13:06.453
If we notify the public,
then the terrorists know
we're onto 'em.

13:06.486 --> 13:09.189
Wouldn't want to give them
a reason to alter their plan
as we know it.

13:09.222 --> 13:12.692
A reason to panic
and detonate right then?

13:12.725 --> 13:15.628
We want to hit 'em before
they know the fight has begun.

13:15.662 --> 13:18.398
Yes. This is
high stakes poker.

13:18.431 --> 13:21.902
High stakes poker, yes.
Play the cards you're dealt.

13:21.935 --> 13:24.905
No. You play the player,
and we don't know who
that is yet. Steven?

13:24.938 --> 13:26.606
Sir?
Get Homeland Security
in here.

13:26.639 --> 13:30.310
Sir, if in the next
few hours, we don't have
them in our sights--

13:30.343 --> 13:33.446
In the next few hours,
we may be at war with Russia.

13:33.480 --> 13:36.383
Sir, word from Moscow.
They're denying any involvement.

13:36.416 --> 13:38.585
They're denying
it's their uranium.

13:38.618 --> 13:41.021
- It may be theirs, but
in the hands of others now?
- Who did control it?

13:41.054 --> 13:42.990
- Former K.G.B. officer.
- What's his name?

13:43.023 --> 13:45.959
- Armen Kochenko.
- And how do we find him?

13:45.993 --> 13:48.962
We snatched him at Grand
Central Station in New York
waiting to board a train.

13:48.996 --> 13:51.031
He'll be on the ground
at Edwards in 90 minutes.

13:55.302 --> 13:57.938
Then I want you
talking to him.

13:57.971 --> 13:59.873
Yes, Mr. President.

13:59.907 --> 14:03.076
Do I make the extent
of my request clear?

14:04.644 --> 14:06.446
Yes, sir. You do.

14:13.020 --> 14:14.988
All right, guys.

14:15.022 --> 14:18.791
Anderson County sheriff
confirms that the vehicle
with matching plates...

14:18.825 --> 14:21.061
is headed north
on the U.S. 127.

14:21.094 --> 14:23.496
Picked up at
the Lawrenceburg tollbooth.

14:23.530 --> 14:27.534
Dirt Diver and Betty Blue
will intersect at Taylorsville.

14:27.567 --> 14:29.937
All right. I'm getting
a second hit now...

14:29.970 --> 14:34.441
on the 18 crossing northeast
into West Virginia.

14:34.474 --> 14:36.977
Must be headed
to Philadelphia or New York.

14:37.010 --> 14:39.046
Picking up
the coordinates now.

14:39.079 --> 14:42.382
If Snake Doctor heads east
and gets off at Blackburn,

14:42.415 --> 14:44.251
he can get in front
of him and fishhook.

14:44.284 --> 14:46.853
How much farther?
About four klicks.

14:46.886 --> 14:49.122
Two lane?
Hold on.

14:49.156 --> 14:51.291
- Look for high ground.
- I'm searching.

14:51.324 --> 14:53.193
- Give me something.
- Trestle bridge.

14:53.226 --> 14:56.896
- That'll do.
- He's passing Beckley now.

14:56.930 --> 14:59.266
- Local units
setting up roadblocks.
- No, no, no, no.

14:59.299 --> 15:01.734
Call 'em off.
Call off the helos too.

15:01.768 --> 15:04.237
- We can tie him off
at Covington Exit.
- Call off all pursuit.

15:04.271 --> 15:06.739
- I want him to think
he's got daylight.
- Roger.

15:06.773 --> 15:08.675
Tallyho!

15:14.747 --> 15:18.618
You know, coming this way
doesn't get him to Texas.

15:18.651 --> 15:23.056
Well, wherever he's headed,
he's about to get slowed down.

15:23.090 --> 15:26.226
Unless he's a suicide bomber.
Maybe they all are.

15:26.259 --> 15:29.997
Hey. Call your family.
Get 'em out of Dallas.

15:30.030 --> 15:33.166
That, uh-- That violates
some protocol, Top.

15:33.200 --> 15:35.835
- Not if it's an order.
- Is it an order?

15:35.868 --> 15:38.338
It is.

15:38.371 --> 15:42.109
- Is it a lawful order?
- Call your family.

15:42.142 --> 15:44.477
- Do you have
a danger code word?
- Yes, I do.

15:44.511 --> 15:46.413
Use it.

15:53.320 --> 15:55.288
[ Vehicle Approaching ]

15:57.991 --> 16:00.160
Thank you very much.
There you go.

16:01.995 --> 16:03.896
He's coming up
the block now.

16:03.930 --> 16:06.199
Blue Suzuki.

16:06.233 --> 16:08.601
- Ah.
- God bless.

16:10.637 --> 16:12.839
Tags match.

16:12.872 --> 16:14.674
Nice and easy.

16:19.446 --> 16:21.848
Go, go!
Move it, move it!

16:21.881 --> 16:24.651
Right there.
[ Grunting ]

16:24.684 --> 16:27.587
Please do not move.

16:27.620 --> 16:30.523
Get them off the sidewalk!
Hey, get back!

16:32.825 --> 16:35.195
[ Men Shouting ]

16:36.963 --> 16:38.598
It's here.

16:40.233 --> 16:42.769
Kim. Kim, listen.
I need you to call
your parents.

16:42.802 --> 16:45.605
- Tell them to put
the kids in the car.
- In the car?

16:45.638 --> 16:48.475
Kim, listen to me.
Tell them to head west
and that you'll meet them.

16:48.508 --> 16:50.710
Wait. Meet-- Meet them where?
What are you talking about?

16:50.743 --> 16:52.512
Alas Babylon.

16:52.545 --> 16:54.781
Did you hear me?

16:54.814 --> 16:57.217
Alas Babylon.
I understand.

16:57.250 --> 17:00.620
Just have them drive
as fast and as far
as they can out of state.

17:00.653 --> 17:04.591
- I understand.
- Get them out of Texas
right now.

17:04.624 --> 17:06.493
- Bob?
- I gotta go.

17:29.949 --> 17:31.784
[ Engine Off ]

17:43.096 --> 17:45.398
[ Screams ]

17:56.042 --> 17:58.077
I tried to take him alive.

18:04.284 --> 18:06.819
Detonator?
No. It's not on him.

18:07.954 --> 18:09.822
Huh?

18:14.294 --> 18:17.264
His target's Philadelphia.
Yeah. Not anymore.

18:17.297 --> 18:19.166
- Give me a hand with this.
- Yeah.

18:19.199 --> 18:21.334
Careful.

18:33.045 --> 18:36.549
Scratch St. Louis
off the target list.

18:36.583 --> 18:38.851
Basic gun-type construction.
High explosive at one end.

18:38.885 --> 18:41.321
Yeah. Uranium core
at the other end.
But which is which?

18:41.354 --> 18:43.423
That's a good question.
Too many wires.

18:43.456 --> 18:46.159
Some decoys,
some booby traps.

18:46.193 --> 18:48.428
It's rigged.
Mmm.

18:48.461 --> 18:50.363
- Okay. Talk me through.
- All right.

18:50.397 --> 18:53.400
Betty Blue, give us
the play-by-play. We'll, uh--
We'll do it together.

18:53.433 --> 18:56.336
Tell Jonas to feel underneath
the cylinder for a device.

18:56.369 --> 18:59.372
Here's the pressure
that you want, as if he's poking
around a throbbing tooth.

18:59.406 --> 19:01.874
You understand?
Careful.

19:06.446 --> 19:09.449
Uh-- See something
that looks like a Bluetooth.
Exactly.

19:09.482 --> 19:11.618
That's the trigger
for the detonator.

19:11.651 --> 19:13.886
- It can be detonated
by a cell phone.
- [ Exhales ]

19:15.988 --> 19:19.259
- Is this thing hot?
- No way to tell
till we open it.

19:20.393 --> 19:23.129
We should move
all those folks back a ways.

19:23.162 --> 19:26.098
Save your strength.
No matter how far they go,
won't make a difference.

19:26.132 --> 19:28.235
[ Radio Chatter ]

19:36.209 --> 19:38.177
This is for
our highly placed friend?

19:38.211 --> 19:40.313
[ Beeping ]
It's an exit strategy.

19:40.347 --> 19:42.949
So where are we sending
the lucky bastard?

19:44.617 --> 19:48.288
Ah. Lovely Caracas.
QuÃ© bueno.

19:49.356 --> 19:51.391
There's one
in there for you too.

19:51.424 --> 19:53.260
- Venezuela?
- [ Phone Beeps ]

19:53.293 --> 19:56.563
The phrase
you're looking for
is "thank you."

19:56.596 --> 19:58.431
Thank you.

20:01.634 --> 20:04.604
Not answering.
Who's not answering?

20:04.637 --> 20:06.873
Other two cars.
Where the hell
is everybody?

20:06.906 --> 20:09.476
Something happen to them?

20:09.509 --> 20:11.844
Hey, you hear
from the others?

20:11.878 --> 20:14.947
All right.
Look, uh, we have a problem.

20:14.981 --> 20:17.049
They may be
locked on to you.

20:17.083 --> 20:19.118
New plan.

20:19.151 --> 20:20.953
[ Screwdriver Whirring ]

20:25.825 --> 20:29.362
Okay. Uh, we're looking
at a green wire...

20:29.396 --> 20:31.864
connects
to a digital timer.

20:31.898 --> 20:34.834
- No. It's redundant.
It's a dummy. Cut it away.
- You sure?

20:34.867 --> 20:37.169
- Cut it and see.
- All right. Hold on.

20:37.203 --> 20:38.705
Stand by.

20:42.041 --> 20:43.776
All right. We're good.

20:44.944 --> 20:46.846
Hold that.

20:49.215 --> 20:51.618
Okay. Cool Breeze.

20:51.651 --> 20:55.955
Have Top look for a
heavily shielded wire beneath
the right side. Mine's yellow.

20:58.458 --> 21:00.059
- Does mine have to be yellow?
- No.

21:00.092 --> 21:04.564
- I have a white one,
heavily shielded.
- Okay.

21:04.597 --> 21:06.766
Look, brothers.
This cut oughta be the one.

21:06.799 --> 21:08.901
I'm gonna keep talking
as I go.

21:08.935 --> 21:13.306
If my comm suddenly goes dead,
tell Snake Doc to cut
the black wire instead.

21:13.340 --> 21:15.308
We're gonna be fine.

21:15.342 --> 21:17.877
[ Chuckles, Grunts ]

21:21.414 --> 21:24.884
I, Charles Lewis Grey,

21:24.917 --> 21:27.654
take you, Joss Morgan,

21:27.687 --> 21:29.889
to be my lawfully wedded wife.

21:29.922 --> 21:33.560
In the presence of God,
our family and friends,

21:33.593 --> 21:36.363
I offer you my solemn vow
to be your faithful partner...

21:36.396 --> 21:39.031
in sickness and in health,

21:39.065 --> 21:40.900
in good times and in bad,

21:47.073 --> 21:50.377
till death do us part.

21:52.712 --> 21:54.914
Buddy, if she won't
marry you, I will.

21:54.947 --> 21:56.683
[ Chuckling ]

21:57.984 --> 21:59.819
Make the cut.

22:02.922 --> 22:05.024
[ Exhales ]

22:05.057 --> 22:06.793
Pager five.
Yeah.

22:10.296 --> 22:12.932
[ Beeps ]

22:18.438 --> 22:20.607
[ Beeps ]

22:23.275 --> 22:26.345
- What?
- Isotope isn't weapons grade.

22:26.379 --> 22:30.817
- It's not uranium?
- Not U-235.

22:30.850 --> 22:34.621
Check Betty Blue's.
Betty Blue, we, uh--
we got a dummy nuke.

22:34.654 --> 22:37.390
What's your readout?
Negative.

22:37.424 --> 22:40.259
- Both are fakes?
- Isn't that clever?

22:40.292 --> 22:42.929
- Three suitcases,
two of them are dummies.
- Yeah.

22:42.962 --> 22:46.966
But the third one,
it's got the magic prize.

22:57.343 --> 23:00.413
[ Door Opens ]

23:00.447 --> 23:03.716
Right now there's
a nuclear device being driven
toward Dallas, Texas.

23:03.750 --> 23:07.119
Call it off.
Whom exactly do you
expect me to call?

23:07.153 --> 23:10.156
Leon Drake, his men
or the bastards
you're working for.

23:10.189 --> 23:12.692
I am retired.
But you know that.

23:12.725 --> 23:14.927
There's a hell of a lot
of former K.G.B.'s
like yourself...

23:14.961 --> 23:17.129
pedaling nukes
for their 401(k)'s.

23:17.163 --> 23:19.365
Better than the stock market.

23:19.398 --> 23:21.033
Call it off.

23:21.067 --> 23:23.436
Even if what you
are saying is correct,

23:23.470 --> 23:25.872
I don't control Drake
or his people.

23:25.905 --> 23:29.408
I'm a blissfully ignorant
middleman.

23:29.442 --> 23:33.245
- But you can lead us to him.
- In exchange for freedom,
I could try to help.

23:33.279 --> 23:36.015
I'm not authorized
to make that deal.

23:36.048 --> 23:39.118
Of course not.
You're not authorized
to make a deal.

23:39.151 --> 23:40.953
That's correct.

23:40.987 --> 23:44.624
Then I suggest you take my offer
to the real power, quickly.

24:03.543 --> 24:05.645
[ Man Chattering ]
Tags match.

24:05.678 --> 24:07.947
Yeah, the engine's still warm.
Must've switched vehicles.

24:07.980 --> 24:10.249
Which means he knows we took
down the other two cars.

24:10.282 --> 24:12.852
Which means he's been
in contact with Drake
and that he knows.

24:12.885 --> 24:15.522
- Pass the word to Snake Doc?
- Yeah. When we touch down
in D.C.

24:15.555 --> 24:18.991
- The car's empty.
- Well, he's not getting far
with a 70-pound duffel bag.

24:19.025 --> 24:21.594
He might have hitched.
There's not much traffic
out here.

24:21.628 --> 24:24.764
Sir, we got a call in.
There's been an incident
up the road a ways.

24:24.797 --> 24:27.066
I don't like the sound
of this already.

24:30.169 --> 24:31.804
[ Police Radio Chatter ]

24:33.139 --> 24:36.475
Carjacked.
Double tap to the chest,
no signs of struggle.

24:36.509 --> 24:38.578
Yeah. Not much
of a fair fight.

24:38.611 --> 24:42.114
Witness inside said she saw
a man with a large duffel
wandering the parking lot.

24:42.148 --> 24:45.952
Run his license, get a make
on his vehicle, see if anybody
saw which way he went.

24:45.985 --> 24:48.888
You know which way.
He's going to Dallas.

24:48.921 --> 24:51.724
How sick is he?
[ Tiffy ] What do you
mean it's closed?

24:51.758 --> 24:54.927
Can you get it open?
Well, can you get one
of the neighbors to help?

24:54.961 --> 24:57.029
No, Mom.
I cannot explain.

24:57.063 --> 25:00.700
But you and the kids need
to get out of there now.

25:00.733 --> 25:04.336
All right.
I'll call you back
in 10 minutes.

25:04.370 --> 25:05.905
And that's closed too?
[ Beeps ]

25:05.938 --> 25:08.007
- He's too sick to travel.
- Your father?

25:08.040 --> 25:11.711
Even if he could,
my mom says the interstate's
closed in the area.

25:11.744 --> 25:13.680
Well, they've closed the
Dallas-Fort Worth Airport.

25:13.713 --> 25:15.615
They've grounded
all planes in or out.

25:15.648 --> 25:20.086
- If they're shutting down
the airports, it must mean--
- I know what it means.

25:20.119 --> 25:22.555
I have to get my kids.

25:22.589 --> 25:26.693
Okay, listen. If I hightail it
now to Van Nuys Airport,
I can get a Lear 35.

25:26.726 --> 25:28.995
Make it to Dallas and back
in five hours.

25:29.028 --> 25:31.163
Who's gonna fly it?
I'll fly it.

25:31.197 --> 25:35.234
If there is a threat,
you can't go flying
into the middle of it.

25:35.267 --> 25:38.638
Yes, I can. Call your parents.
Tell them to get ready.

25:38.671 --> 25:40.707
Joss, they've closed
the airports.

25:40.740 --> 25:44.644
Well, then I'll
have to use my own.

25:52.852 --> 25:54.854
All right.
Your deal's approved.

25:54.887 --> 25:58.357
But only after we get Drake and
only if we stop the remaining
bomb from detonating.

25:58.390 --> 26:00.326
Then we go.

26:00.359 --> 26:03.095
This is my best man.
Where do we find Drake
and the bomb?

26:03.129 --> 26:05.932
I must go with you.
If I'm not there,
Drake won't show.

26:05.965 --> 26:08.400
I don't believe
that's how this mission
is going to proceed.

26:08.434 --> 26:11.771
You tell us the location,
we'll decide who goes with.

26:11.804 --> 26:15.642
We have to hurry. If you don't
have me on a plane out of here
within the hour,

26:15.675 --> 26:17.744
you will miss him
and lose your bomb.

26:17.777 --> 26:20.079
[ Shouts ]
Where is it?
You have a quick temper.

26:20.112 --> 26:22.114
I have a quick temper
and unofficial authorization
to kill you...

26:22.148 --> 26:23.850
if you don't tell me
where that bomb is!

26:23.883 --> 26:25.985
You are quick
to lose your temper.

26:26.018 --> 26:28.755
That's one of the many things
your file says.
My file, huh?

26:28.788 --> 26:30.857
The one back in Russia.

26:30.890 --> 26:33.826
You think
someone in your position
doesn't have a file?

26:33.860 --> 26:36.095
[ Chuckles ]
You drink too much.
You've made mistakes.

26:36.128 --> 26:39.966
- You've had failures.
- What do you know
about my failures?

26:39.999 --> 26:42.501
I know they led
to the events of today.
How's that?

26:42.534 --> 26:44.771
Venezuela.

26:46.138 --> 26:50.009
Venezuela?
You had a mission to
assassinate President Ortiz.

26:50.042 --> 26:53.012
What?
Colonel, word travels.

26:53.045 --> 26:56.115
Your mission had flaws.
Your men failed.

26:56.148 --> 26:59.151
And worst of all,
they showed their hand.

26:59.185 --> 27:02.221
President Ortiz
was displeased.

27:02.254 --> 27:05.624
President Ortiz?
Who do you think paid
for the uranium?

27:05.658 --> 27:09.028
Who do you think
contracted Drake to kill
your vice president?

27:09.061 --> 27:11.230
That madman from Venezuela.

27:12.631 --> 27:14.801
You understand we're
just two men talking.

27:14.834 --> 27:17.770
Of course, if you had
succeeded in killing him,

27:17.804 --> 27:21.473
your country wouldn't be
in this position.

27:21.507 --> 27:25.712
Now get me on that airplane,
or you're about to lose
one of your cities.

27:31.017 --> 27:33.619
Alpha Team
touched down in Sherwood.
En route now.

27:33.652 --> 27:37.757
F.B.I. out of Little Rock is
reporting the vehicle belonging
to the carjack victim...

27:37.790 --> 27:40.760
is entering Route 67.

27:40.793 --> 27:43.629
Betty Blue, local units
clearing the highway now.

27:43.662 --> 27:47.466
- All right. Give it to me.
- Up ahead, hard right
onto Wildwood.

27:47.499 --> 27:51.170
- [ Tires Squealing ]
- Think I can take him out
with a pit maneuver?

27:51.203 --> 27:53.840
Last resort. We don't want
to upset the package.

27:53.873 --> 27:56.442
- He's heading towards downtown.
- Yeah, yeah. We're pushing it.
We're pushing it.

28:02.348 --> 28:05.918
That's him up ahead.
Yeah, that's right.
Come on. Go for it.

28:13.092 --> 28:15.527
- He spotted us.
- If it detonates in the city--

28:15.561 --> 28:18.397
Yeah, I know. I know.

28:18.430 --> 28:20.767
Get me a little closer.

28:23.803 --> 28:25.304
- Steady.
- Take him out!

28:25.337 --> 28:27.106
Might upset the cargo.
Then we've all had it.

28:27.139 --> 28:29.275
Lot worse
if it happens downtown.

28:29.308 --> 28:32.144
You are one altruistic
son of a bitch.

28:36.482 --> 28:38.417
He's coming up on the right.

28:40.519 --> 28:43.089
Steady! Steady!

28:43.122 --> 28:44.490
Steady.

28:55.067 --> 28:57.937
- [ Mack ] Here we go!
- [ Bob ] Hold on!

28:59.438 --> 29:01.808
[ Tires Screeching ]

29:09.515 --> 29:11.483
Well, no mushroom cloud.

29:12.985 --> 29:15.521
Three cars down. No nukes.

29:15.554 --> 29:17.256
Where's the uranium?

29:24.330 --> 29:27.599
[ Kochenko ]
Do you have the plane ready?
Yeah, it's ready.

29:27.633 --> 29:30.636
- Question first.
- You don't have time
for questions.

29:30.669 --> 29:32.771
You were picked up
at Grand Central Station.
Yes.

29:32.805 --> 29:35.942
With a ticket to Chicago
in your pocket.
That is also correct.

29:35.975 --> 29:37.709
Well, here's my question.

29:37.743 --> 29:40.212
Why did you get to the station
three hours before your train
departed?

29:40.246 --> 29:42.314
Because I did not want
to miss my train.

29:42.348 --> 29:45.217
Are you going to let
a nuclear bomb explode
in your country...

29:45.251 --> 29:48.354
as this man satisfies
his curiosity?

29:48.387 --> 29:51.357
You know, your concern
for our country's safety
is touching.

29:51.390 --> 29:54.293
But I think the ticket
to Chicago's crap.

29:54.326 --> 29:56.929
Where were you really headed?
You would do well
to listen to me.

29:56.963 --> 30:02.001
Your country is in danger.
We have new intel that the bomb
was intended for Boston.

30:02.034 --> 30:06.005
We don't need you.
You don't know
where in Boston.

30:06.038 --> 30:08.540
Fly me there, and I might
still be able to stop it.

30:08.574 --> 30:12.912
There is no
new intel about Boston.
You're lying.

30:12.945 --> 30:16.282
The nuke is headed here
to Washington, isn't it?

30:16.315 --> 30:19.818
The one thing
you were desperate for
is to get out of here.

30:19.852 --> 30:22.588
We're in a blast zone,
aren't we?

30:22.621 --> 30:25.157
[ Beeping ]

30:25.191 --> 30:28.494
Redcap, cancel the plane.
We won't be needing it.

30:28.527 --> 30:31.630
You are going to lose
millions of lives if you
don't get me on that plane.

30:31.663 --> 30:35.501
No. I think you're gonna
lose yours right along with
the rest of us! Come on!

30:35.534 --> 30:39.005
- Where are you taking him?
- We're going for a picnic
out on the Mall.

30:39.038 --> 30:43.309
Nice view of the D.C. skyline.
Me and him, we're gonna ride out
this storm together.

30:43.342 --> 30:46.678
Yes! All right!
The bomb is coming here
to Washington.

30:46.712 --> 30:49.048
- When?
- Soon. Maybe already here.

30:49.081 --> 30:51.984
I was to meet him,
leave the country with him.

30:52.018 --> 30:54.653
- Who? Leon Drake?
- Yes.

30:54.686 --> 30:56.588
Meet him where?

31:02.962 --> 31:06.198
[ Saw Buzzing ]

31:06.232 --> 31:09.568
[ Man Praying, Indistinct ]

31:10.636 --> 31:13.472
- Your friend not here?
- [ Phone Beeping ]

31:15.574 --> 31:18.344
I think
the Tomb of the Unknowns
is around here somewhere.

31:29.989 --> 31:32.391
Any hints on who
we might be waiting on?

31:33.993 --> 31:37.429
Someone once said--
[ Beeps ]

31:37.463 --> 31:39.565
Who was it?

31:39.598 --> 31:41.900
"During wartime,

31:41.934 --> 31:44.236
"truth is so precious...

31:44.270 --> 31:49.041
that she should
always be attended
by a bodyguard of lies."

31:49.075 --> 31:53.980
I believe it was Churchill
who said it... on D-Day.

31:55.781 --> 31:57.984
Very impressive.

32:11.030 --> 32:15.201
[ Loud Grunting ]

32:16.468 --> 32:17.970
[ Woman Gasps ]

32:18.004 --> 32:20.006
[ Shouts ]

32:24.710 --> 32:27.346
[ Gunshots ]
[ Woman ]
Someone's shot!

32:27.379 --> 32:30.316
- Oh, my God! Oh!
- [ Man ] What in the world?

32:40.026 --> 32:43.029
- Thanks.
- Well, I haven't
saved us yet.

32:43.062 --> 32:44.963
The bomb's here somewhere.

32:44.997 --> 32:47.166
- What about
the other three cars?
- Decoys, all of them.

32:47.199 --> 32:49.735
Drake said we were here
to meet his mole, his insider.

32:49.768 --> 32:52.238
There is no mole.
He was gonna kill you and
make you look responsible.

32:52.271 --> 32:55.941
- There's no bomb in the car.
- It's here! Somewhere where
Drake could get at it.

32:55.974 --> 32:59.578
It's not in the car.
It's a part of the car.

32:59.611 --> 33:01.513
This is ground zero.

33:05.917 --> 33:09.321
[ TV ] ...has yet to approve--
Nothing on the news about
an incident or attack in Texas.

33:09.355 --> 33:11.290
Why hasn't Joss called?

33:11.323 --> 33:13.192
She probably
left your parents'
a little while go.

33:13.225 --> 33:16.395
- Maybe they're back
in the air already.
- Maybe Molly has it right.

33:16.428 --> 33:18.564
- Look, we've been here before.
- Exactly.

33:18.597 --> 33:22.734
And we'll be here again if we
keep letting the army push us
around the board like checkers.

33:22.768 --> 33:25.704
You see your kids,
and this feeling
will just fade away.

33:25.737 --> 33:28.440
No. It won't, Tiffy.

33:30.042 --> 33:32.944
[ Sighs ]
Say it.

33:32.978 --> 33:35.547
Whatever's bothering you,
just say it.

33:38.717 --> 33:41.320
Since Bob and I joined the Unit,
one thing gave me comfort.

33:41.353 --> 33:44.223
- Do you know what that is?
- No.

33:44.256 --> 33:47.559
If Molly and Jonas
could make it,
so could Bob and me.

33:47.593 --> 33:52.931
And now she's gone and
said out loud the one thing
we do not ask our husbands.

33:52.964 --> 33:54.766
You tell me what that is.

33:56.068 --> 33:58.704
Which do you love more,

33:58.737 --> 34:01.473
the job or me?

34:01.507 --> 34:02.774
That's right.

34:11.417 --> 34:13.452
Find anything?
Not yet.

34:13.485 --> 34:16.122
The others
were 70 pound cylinder--

34:16.155 --> 34:18.224
The drive shaft.

34:20.226 --> 34:23.162
- Fresh welding.
- Any trigger device?

34:23.195 --> 34:25.597
The other three
were Bluetooth,
call activated.

34:25.631 --> 34:29.000
Drake's cell.
He dialed someone before.

34:29.034 --> 34:31.103
He's already activated it.

34:31.137 --> 34:34.473
- Then the clock's ticking.
- He would've given himself time
to get out of the blast range.

34:34.506 --> 34:36.375
No way to know
how much time that gives us.

34:36.408 --> 34:38.410
Time to earn our pay.

34:38.444 --> 34:41.347
Listen, Top. If the bomb
is in the driveshaft,

34:41.380 --> 34:43.615
it's gonna be
the same gun-type design.

34:43.649 --> 34:47.286
- The target at one end and the
uranium bullet at the other.
- What about the detonator?

34:47.319 --> 34:50.322
No time. Your only choice is
to cut the cylinder in half.
The drive shaft?

34:50.356 --> 34:53.559
Yeah. Break the shaft
in the middle. Keep the bullet
from hitting the uranium core.

34:53.592 --> 34:57.095
It won't disarm the bomb,
but it'll keep it
from going nuclear.

34:57.129 --> 34:59.498
I've got nothing
that'll cut steel.

34:59.531 --> 35:01.867
I got it.

35:01.900 --> 35:05.304
Okay. You're gonna have to
get under that car somehow.
You're gonna have to jack it up.

35:08.274 --> 35:10.642
Well, we've come
to the right place.
Hold one.

35:14.446 --> 35:17.349
- [ Metal Clanging ]
- [ Car Engine Starts ]

35:33.732 --> 35:35.601
[ Car Door Closes ]

35:45.944 --> 35:47.846
Light.

35:50.382 --> 35:52.518
Betty Blue, we're a go.

35:55.787 --> 35:57.989
[ Bob ]
Jonas, before you do it,
know this.

35:58.023 --> 36:01.893
Once you make that first cut,
you're gonna be exposed
to radiation.

36:01.927 --> 36:03.529
How much?

36:03.562 --> 36:06.432
Ninety seconds.
Ninety seconds.

36:06.465 --> 36:09.301
Any more than that,
and the radiation will--
I get it.

36:09.335 --> 36:11.570
Don't want to dig
my own grave.

36:11.603 --> 36:13.905
Godspeed, man.

36:13.939 --> 36:15.774
[ Whirring ]

36:24.583 --> 36:27.786
Thirty seconds gone.
Almost there.

36:27.819 --> 36:29.355
Come on, come on!

36:31.923 --> 36:34.626
[ Clanging ]
Ah!

36:34.660 --> 36:37.028
Saw's caught in the cut.
Push it!

36:37.062 --> 36:39.365
Fifty seconds gone!

36:41.900 --> 36:43.802
[ Grunts ]

36:46.272 --> 36:48.907
Brake's slipping!
The car's gonna fall on you!

36:52.077 --> 36:54.680
- [ Grunts ]
